FBIS4-48199 "drafr094_b_94005" FBIS-AFR-94-094 Daily Report 15 May 1994 EAST AFRICA Tanzania Evacuation Efforts Continue Evacuation Efforts Continue EA1505130894 Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania Network in Swahili 0330 GMT 15 May 94 EA1505130894 Dar es Salaam Radio Tanzania Network Swahili BFN [From the press review] [Text] Efforts to evacuate Tanzanian nationals in Rwanda continue. The government said it was making further efforts to repatriate 40 Tanzanian nationals who have been stranded in Rwanda following intensified ethnic clashes. Speaking in a telephone interview yesterday following reports that 40 Tanzanians were stranded in offices previously used by Tanzania's diplomatic mission in Rwanda, the permanent secretary in the Ministry of Foreign Affairs and International Cooperation, Dr. Ibrahim Msabaha, said the government had already made contacts with various NGO's, including the Red Cross, asking them to provide assistance in the form of food and medicines to the Tanzanians. Besides this, the government has also contacted the French and Belgian Embassies in Rwanda to look into the possibility of transporting the Tanzanians by road. More than 40 national flags were sent to Rwanda the day before yesterday to be used by vehicles that would provide transport to the Tanzanians.
